gallery/oco0x2O</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wAX13Gr.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Literally just stoop up and walked away from a co-worker who continued to talk to me (about work) after I politely said I was on my unpaid lunch break, but we could talk after I clock back in. 

I value my time off from work. Whether that’s my 30 minute lunch, PTO or paid holidays. I’m certainly not here by choice.  I’ve been forced back after the company decided Covid wasn’t real anymore (it very much is, but I’d like to stay employed so here I am back in office). Please leave me alone when I’m not getting paid to deal with you. I’ll do the same for you.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/oco0x2O</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[danrathernot]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Things seen this week during structural assessments!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/WjAADO4</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Uc09fvk.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We saw this interesting deck out on one of our assessments.

Jenga but 100x bigger!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/X4VlG4A.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This home’s access door to their California basement was located in the bathroom. 

I'm sure they dominated at hide & seek.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/aVspx0v.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Efflorescence is the white chalky powder that you might find on the surface of a concrete or brick wall. It's a sign of moisture intrusion that could lead to major structural issues if not checked out.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/m4ylM4X.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Rusted pipes pose a significant threat to your structure’s foundation.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lifNrmB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>If not taken care of, the post will slip out of place and the girder above will lose crucial support.

Regular maintenance on your home is important for this reason. Taking care of the little things now can prevent bigger problems in the future</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7Y4lpYu.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>How close I am to losing my cool.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/evT01lI.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Rusty pipes soon flake and corrode, creating leaks. Some leaks pose a more significant risk than others.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ESaiN1O.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Leaking pipes can flood the foundation of a building. This could result in cracks in the concrete, significant mold presence, or even the sinking of the foundation. The longer the leaks continue, the greater the damage that they can do to your foundations.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WOWd08g.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Is it still worth $250,000?</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/WjAADO4</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[AlphaStructural]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>super mega chad energy</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/d4O16pO</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3eoxvbn.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tmWqsPX.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/d4O16pO</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[eyedontcare]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Sus Memes v77</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/479jOXA</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SIyqZDu.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Jesus fucking Christ. I’d say this couldn’t be real but I’ve been hit 